  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter and NFI support for Flood and Landslide Affected Population in South-Western and Central Provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving assistance to 42,500 vulnerable people affected by the floods, landslides and heavy rains in Matara and Rathnapura districts in Sri Lanka. With this CERF grant, IOM will procure and distribute 2,100 NFI kits and 1,700 shelter kits, as well as provide some 3,700 cash transfers totalling $294,750 for shelter and NFI assistance during a four month timeframe.</narrative>
  </description>
